Install Sass - Windows
    1. install ruby by ruby-installer
    2. install sass
        $ gem install sass
    3. install compass
        $ gem install compass

Install Sass - Ubuntu 14.04
    1. install rvm
        $ gpg --keyserver hkp://keys.gnupg.net --recv-keys 409B6B1796C275462A1703113804BB82D39DC0E3
        $ \curl -sSL https://get.rvm.io | bash -s stable
    2. restart the terminal
    3. install latest ruby by rvm
        $ rvm install ruby
    4. use ruby (suppose the latest version of ruby is 2.3.0)
        $ rvm --default use 2.3.0
    5. install sass
        $ gem install sass
    6. install compass
        $ gem install compass
Test
    1. test rvm
        $ rvm -v
        1-1. if not work try restart the termainal
        1-2. for some case go to Edit > Profile Preferences, Title and Command tag, and check the Run command as a login shell
    2. test ruby
        $ ruby -v
        2-1. if not work try rvm use
    3. test sass
        $ sass -v
        3-1. if not work look up the install log for error message
    4. test compass
        $ compass -v
        4-1. if not work look up the install log for error message